edential storage\n- Add API key resolution logic\n\n## T3: Registry Client\n- Create `cmd/cli/internal/registry.py`\n- Implement upload method\n- Add progress tracking\n\n## T4: Package Validation\n- Validate package file path\n- Check file format","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775894266512,"end":1775894266532}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775894266535,"sessionID":"ses_284747457ffeiwSMHZcOFUQyO2","part":{"id":"prt_d7b8bf4c2001fEa0FuEG3A4RhX","messageID":"msg_d7b8be11b001fQqOrgqdn1fuK5","sessionID":"ses_284747457ffeiwSMHZcOFUQyO2","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-022: CLI publish 命令 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: This document describes the delta specification for implementing the `publish` command in the AgentCube CLI.\n5: \n6: ## Current State\n7: - The CLI framework exists with command structure\n8: - The `pack` command (AR-020) creates distributable archives\n9: - No publish functionality exists yet\n10: \n11: ## Target State\n12: A fully functional `publish` command that:\n13: - Uploads packaged agents to the AgentCube registry\n14: - Handles authentication securely\n15: - Provides upload progress feedback\n16: - Validates packages before publishing\n17: \n18: ## Delta Analysis\n19: \n20: ### New Components\n21: 1. **Publish Command Module** (`cmd/cli/publish.py`)\n22:    - CLI interface for publish command\n23:    - Argument parsing and validation\n24:    - Integration with upload logic\n25: \n26: 2. **Registry Client** (`cmd/cli/internal/registry.py`)\n27:    - HTTP client for registry API\n28:    - Authentication handling\n29:    - Upload request construction\n30: \n31: 3. **Authentication Module** (`cmd/cli/internal/auth.py`)\n32:    - API key/token management\n33:    - Credential storage and retrieval\n34: \n35: ### Modified Components\n36: - `cmd/cli/main.py` - Add publish subcommand\n37: \n38: ### Dependencies\n39: - Requires AR-020 (pack command) for package creation\n40: - Uses existing CLI framework\n41: \n42: ## Interface Specification\n43: \n44: ### Command Signature\n45: ```bash\n46: agentcube publish [OPTIONS] <package-file>\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ### Options\n50: - `--registry, -r`: Target registry URL (default: https://registry.agentcube.io)\n51: - `--api-key, -k`: API key for authentication\n52: - `--dry-run`: Validate without uploading\n53: - `--verbose, -v`: Verbose output\n54: \n55: ### Exit Codes\n56: - `0`: Success\n57: - `1`: General error\n58: - `2`: Authentication failed\n59: - `3`: Package validation failed\n60: - `4`: Upload failed\n61: \n62: ## Implementation Notes\n63: - Follow existing CLI patterns from other commands\n64: - Use streaming upload for large packages\n65: - Implement exponential backoff for retries\n\n(End of file - total 65 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-022: CLI publish 命令 — Delta Spec\n\n## Overview\nThis document describes the delta specification for implementing the `publish` command in the AgentCube CLI.\n\n## Current State\n- The CLI framework exists with command structure\n- The `pack` command (AR-020) creates distributable archives\n- No publish functionality exists yet\n\n## Target State\nA fully functional `publish` command that:\n- Uploads packaged agents to the AgentCube registry\n- Handles authentication securely\n- Provides upload progress feedback\n- Validates packages before publishing\n\n## Delta Analysis\n\n### New Components","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775894266516,"end":1775894266533}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775894266536,"sessionID":"ses_284747457ffeiwSMHZcOFUQyO2","part":{"id":"prt_d7b8bf9c2001dWI7b6fFFlYnuq","messageID":"msg_d7b8be11b001fQqOrgqdn1fuK5","sessionID":"ses_284747457ffeiwSMHZcOFUQyO2","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/tests.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/tests.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-022: CLI publish 命令 — Test Specification\n2: \n3: ## Unit Tests\n4: \n5: ### Authentication Tests\n6: - `test_auth_loads_from_file`: Credentials load from file\n7: - `test_auth_falls_back_to_env`: Env var fallback works\n8: - `test_auth_missing_raises_error`: Error on missing credentials\n9: \n10: ### Registry Client Tests\n11: - `test_upload_sends_correct_headers`: Headers include auth\n12: - `test_upload_streams_file`: File streamed correctly\n13: - `test_upload_reports_progress`: Progress callback invoked\n14: - `test_upload_handles_errors`: Error responses handled\n15: \n16: ### Command Tests\n17: - `test_publish_validates_args`: Invalid args rejected\n18: - `test_publish_checks_file_exists`: Missing file reported\n19: - `test_publish_dry_run_no_upload`: Dry run skips upload\n20: \n21: ## Integration Tests\n22: \n23: ### Happy Path\n24: - `test_publish_success`: Complete publish flow\n25: - `test_publish_with_progress`: Progress shown correctly\n26: \n27: ### Error Scenarios\n28: - `test_publish_auth_failure`: 401 handled gracefully\n29: - `test_publish_invalid_package`: Validation errors reported\n30: - `test_publish_network_error`: Connection failures handled\n31: \n32: ## Test Data\n33: - Valid package file fixture\n34: - Invalid package file fixture\n35: - Mock registry server\n\n(End of file - total 35 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-022: CLI publish 命令 — Test Specification\n\n## Unit Tests\n\n### Authentication Tests\n- `test_auth_loads_from_file`: Credentials load from file\n- `test_auth_falls_back_to_env`: Env var fallback works\n- `test_auth_missing_raises_error`: Error on missing credentials\n\n### Registry Client Tests\n- `test_upload_sends_correct_headers`: Headers include auth\n- `test_upload_streams_file`: File streamed correctly\n- `test_upload_reports_progress`: Progress callback invoked\n- `test_upload_handles_errors`: Error responses handled\n\n### Command Tests\n- `test_publish_validates_args`: Invalid args rejected\n- `test_publish_checks_file_exists`: Missing file reported\n- `test_publish_dry_run_no_upload`: Dry run skips upload\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/tests.md","time":{"start":1775894266518,"end":1775894266535}}}}
